      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even a small glass of wine can interact unpredictably and dangerously with diazepam. Alcohol slows down the central nervous system, and when combined with a benzodiazepine, it significantly increases the risk of sedation and breathing difficulties, regardless of how little you think you are drinking. For your safety, it is crucial to avoid alcohol completely while taking this prescription. If sleep is an issue, please check with your doctor about non-alcoholic relaxation aids or timing adjustments.",
